content.raw: Yes, that's definitely a typo - though it's not new so not much to worry about. That exception catching block is pretty useless, it only runs if the HDF5 file cannot be opened (in which case it doesn't make any sense to proceed!), so it just shouldn't exist. I might fix it, but more likely It'll vanish next time the queue manager is refactored, which is long overdue.
